node.text:
The journey of conception, all the way through to birth, is like training wheels for becoming a mother. It prepares you for what you need to embrace as a parent—surrender.

There is a spiritual way to travel the path to parenthood that is backed with faith and miracles. Take it from me, I know how hard this journey can be. But today I’m here to remind you of the miracles. I’ve been there. It took me three years to conceive my son. I spent 2020 in and out of the fertility clinic doing IVF for a second child. I experienced postpartum depression that rocked me to my core. But no matter how hard the journey has been for me, there was light on the other side. If it weren’t for my spiritual faith and commitment to surrender, I wouldn’t be able to share this episode with you today. 

May this prayer open you up to the radical acceptance that being a mother is a transformational practice of surrender.

Take a moment, take a deep breath in, and pray with me. 

This week's episode of Dear Gabby is dedicated to The Spiritual Path to Becoming a Mother! 🎙Check out the episode now on Apple Podcast / Spotify or at the link! 🔗 in bio @gabbybernstein

One of the most sacred relationships in my life is with my therapist of nearly a decade. 

She practices a transformational style of therapy called Internal Family Systems (IFS). 

This therapy changed my life.

If you’ve been listening to Dear Gabby, you’ve heard me refer to IFS and even use it. I love it so much that I’m enrolled to take the Level 1 training! 

So when it came time to record episodes of Dear Gabby, Richard Schwartz, the founder of @internalfamilysystems was at the TOP of my list for BIG TALK conversations. 

And today I’m sharing a DEEP dive conversation into IFS and how it literally flips the script on traditional therapy practices!
 
Listen to the episode now on Apple, Spotify or at the link in bio @gabbybernstein 

You’ll learn:
An introduction to IFS 
The 3 types of parts we all have
Why we are so reactive when we’re triggered
Why we sometimes turn to addictive behavior 
The intersection between IFS and spirituality
What it means when we spiritually bypass 
This episode will help you honor all the different parts of who you are … 

You know how sometimes it feels like there are different parts of you that show up at different times? 

Like when you’re super annoyed with a loved one and you lash out. 

Or when you’re embarrassed and you recoil into a fearful place. 

Have you ever said, “A part of me wants to just {insert angry response here}.”

This episode will help you understand these reactions and show you the MOST transformational way to work with all the parts of who you are. 

Learn about the therapy that changed my life forever. >>> 
Listen to the episode now on Apple, Spotify or at the link in bio @gabbybernstein 

Oh and >>>>> You’ll want to listen allllll the way through this BIG TALK!

Stick around to the end to hear Richard walk us through a beautiful meditation. It’s such an amazing experience!

Press play for one of the most transformational conversations of my life.
